gsmpServiceMIB.name: gsmpServiceMIB

revisions.description: Initial revision, published as part of RFC XXXX.

gsmpServiceMIB.contactinfo: Editor: YoungWook Cha Email: ywcha@andong.ac.kr Editor: TaeHyun Kwon Email: freeman@comeng.andong.ac.kr
gsmpServiceMIB.description: This MIB contains managed object definitions for network management services in General Switch Management Protocol (GSMP) Interface.

Label.name: Label
Label.description: This value represents an label as defined in [RFC3292].

Owner.name: Owner
Owner.description: The entity that originally created the object in question. The values of this enumeration are defined as follows: other(1) - This is used when an entity which has not been enumerated in this textual convention but which is known by the agent. snmp(2) - The Simple Network Management Protocol was used to configure this object initially. ldp(3) - The Label Distribution Protocol was used to configure this object initially. rsvp(4) - The Resource Reservation Protocol was used to configure this object initially. crldp(5) - The Constraint-Based Label Distribution Protocol was used to configure this object initially. policyAgent(6) - A policy agent (perhaps in combination with one of the above protocols) was used to configure this object initially. unknown(7) - the agent cannot discern which component created the object.

gsmpSwitchConfTable.name: gsmpSwitchConfTable
gsmpSwitchConfTable.description: This table represents the information of switch configuration.

gsmpSwitchConfEntry.name: gsmpSwitchConfEntry
gsmpSwitchConfEntry.description: The entry of this table is mapped with the each switch partition.

gsmpSwitchPartitionIndex.name: gsmpSwitchPartitionIndex
gsmpSwitchPartitionIndex.description: This is unique index for an entry in the gsmpSwitchConfEntry.

gsmpSwitchConfMtype1.name: gsmpSwitchConfMtype1
gsmpSwitchConfMtype1.description: In the request, this object contains the requested QoS configuration type. In the response, this object contains the accepted QoS configuration type. 0 : Indicates use of the default GSMP model 1 : Indicates use of IEEE qGSMP model 2-200 : Reserved 201-255 : Experimental

gsmpSwitchConfMtype2.name: gsmpSwitchConfMtype2
gsmpSwitchConfMtype2.description: If the switch can not support the requested OoS configuration type in gsmpSwitchConfMtype1, it negotiates the QoS model with the manager by offering up to three additional MType

gsmpSwitchConfMtype3.name: gsmpSwitchConfMtype3
gsmpSwitchConfMtype3.description: If the switch can not support the requested OoS configuration type in gsmpSwitchConfMtype1, it negotiates the QoS model with the manager by offering up to three additional Mtype

gsmpSwitchConfMtype4.name: gsmpSwitchConfMtype4
gsmpSwitchConfMtype4.description: If the switch can not support the requested OoS configuration type in gsmpSwitchConfMtype1, it negotiates the QoS model with the manager by offering up to three additional Mtype

gsmpSwitchConfFirmVer.name: gsmpSwitchConfFirmVer
gsmpSwitchConfFirmVer.description: The version number of the switch control firmware installed.

gsmpSwitchConfWindowSize.name: gsmpSwitchConfWindowSize
gsmpSwitchConfWindowSize.description: The maximum number of unacknowledged request messages that may be transmitted by the controller without the possibility of loss.

gsmpSwitchConfSwitchType.name: gsmpSwitchConfSwitchType
gsmpSwitchConfSwitchType.description: A 16-bit value allocated by the manufacturer of the switch. When this value is combined with the OUI from the gsmpSwitchConfSwitchName, the product is uniquely identified.

gsmpSwitchConfSwitchName.name: gsmpSwitchConfSwitchName
gsmpSwitchConfSwitchName.description: This object is a 48-bit quantity. A 48-bit IEEE 802 MAC address, if available, may be used.

gsmpSwitchConfMaxReservation.name: gsmpSwitchConfMaxReservation
gsmpSwitchConfMaxReservation.description: The maximum number of reservations that the switch can support. A value of 0 indicates that the switch does not support reservations.

gsmpInterfaceConfTable.name: gsmpInterfaceConfTable
gsmpInterfaceConfTable.description: This table represents the configuration information of a single switch port.

gsmpInterfaceConfEntry.name: gsmpInterfaceConfEntry
gsmpInterfaceConfEntry.description: An entry in this table represents the configuration information of a single switch port.

gsmpInterfaceConfIndex.name: gsmpInterfaceConfIndex
gsmpInterfaceConfIndex.description: This is a unique index for an entry in the gsmpInterfaceConfTable.

gsmpPortType.name: gsmpPortType
gsmpPortType.description: This object represents the port type.

gsmpPortStatus.name: gsmpPortStatus
gsmpPortStatus.description: This object indicates the port status.

gsmpLineType.name: gsmpLineType
gsmpLineType.description: This object represents the type of physical transmission interface for this port. PortType = Unknown: other(1) PortType = MPLS: ethernetCsmacd(2), ppp(3) PortType = ATM: atm(4) PortType = FR: frameRelayService(5)

gsmpFunctionType.name: gsmpFunctionType
gsmpFunctionType.description: It specifies the action to be taken by the switch. The specified action will be taken regardless of the current status of the port.

gsmpLineStatus.name: gsmpLineStatus
gsmpLineStatus.description: It defines the status of the physical transmission medium connected to the port. The defined values of the Line Status field are: up(1): The line is able to both send and receive. When the line status changes to Up from either the down or test states, a new port session number MUST be generated. down(2): The line is unable either to send or receive or both. Test(3): The port or line is in a test mode, for example, power-on test.

gsmpPriorties.name: gsmpPriorties
gsmpPriorties.description: This object represents the number of different priority levels that this output port can assign to connections. Zero is invalid in this field.

gsmpPhysicalSlotNumber.name: gsmpPhysicalSlotNumber
gsmpPhysicalSlotNumber.description: The physical location of the slot in which the port is located.

gsmpPhysicalPortNumber.name: gsmpPhysicalPortNumber
gsmpPhysicalPortNumber.description: The physical location of the port within the slot in which the port is located. The Physical Port Number is not used by the GSMP protocol. It is provided to assist network management in functions such as logging, port naming, and graphical representation.

gsmpMinLabel.name: gsmpMinLabel
gsmpMinLabel.description: The minimum label value in the range.

gsmpMaxLabel.name: gsmpMaxLabel
gsmpMaxLabel.description: The maximum label value in the range.

gsmpRemainingLabels.name: gsmpRemainingLabels
gsmpRemainingLabels.description: The maximum number of remaining labels that could be requested for allocation on the specified port.

gsmpConnectionReplace.name: gsmpConnectionReplace
gsmpConnectionReplace.description: It indicates that a switch controller requests the switch port to support the mechanism of connection replacement.

gsmpDuration.name: gsmpDuration
gsmpDuration.description: It is the length of time in seconds, that any of the loopback states remain in operation.

gsmpEventSequenceNumber.name: gsmpEventSequenceNumber
gsmpEventSequenceNumber.description: This object represents the current value of the event sequence number of the switch port. This number is set to zero when the port is initialed.

gsmpEventFlags.name: gsmpEventFlags
gsmpEventFlags.description: It is used to reset the event flags.

gsmpFlowControlFlags.name: gsmpFlowControlFlags
gsmpFlowControlFlags.description: It is used to indicate whether the flow control mechanism is turned on or not.

gsmpTransmitDataRate.name: gsmpTransmitDataRate
gsmpTransmitDataRate.description: It is used to set the output data rate of the output port. cells/s for PortType = ATM bytes/s for PortType = FR bytes/s for PortType = MPLS

gsmpReceiveDataRate.name: gsmpReceiveDataRate
gsmpReceiveDataRate.description: The maximum rate of data that may arrive at the input port. cells/s for PortType = ATM bytes/s for PortType = FR bytes/s for PortType = MPLS

gsmpServiceTable.name: gsmpServiceTable
gsmpServiceTable.description: This table represents the list of services and their associated parameters, which are supported by the switch.

gsmpServiceEntry.name: gsmpServiceEntry
gsmpServiceEntry.description: The entry of this table represents the list of services and their associated parameters, which are supported by the switch.

gsmpServiceId.name: gsmpServiceId
gsmpServiceId.description: This object represents the identifier of the service supported by the switch.

gsmpCapSetId.name: gsmpCapSetId
gsmpCapSetId.description: A capability set contains a set of parameters that describe the QoS parameter values and traffic controls that apply to an instance of the service.

gsmpTrafficControls.name: gsmpTrafficControls
gsmpTrafficControls.description: Identifies the availability of traffic controls within the capability set. U: Usage Parameter Control D: Packet Discard I: Ingress Shaping E: Egress Shaping, Peak Rate S: Egress Traffic Shaping, Sustainable Rate V: VC Merge

gsmpCellLossRatio.name: gsmpCellLossRatio
gsmpCellLossRatio.description: It indicates the cell loss ratio parameter guaranteed by the switch for the specified service.

gsmpCellTransferDelay.name: gsmpCellTransferDelay
gsmpCellTransferDelay.description: The value of this object is expressed in units of microseconds.

gsmpCellDelayVariation.name: gsmpCellDelayVariation
gsmpCellDelayVariation.description: It represents the peak-to-peak cell delay variation. The CDV value is expressed in units of microseconds.

gsmpFrequency.name: gsmpFrequency
gsmpFrequency.description: Frequency applies to the MPLS CR-LDP service. Valid values of this object are: 0 - Very frequent 1 - Frequent 2 - Unspecified

gsmpPortServiceMapTable.name: gsmpPortServiceMapTable
gsmpPortServiceMapTable.description: This table represents the service lists, which are supported by the specific port.

gsmpPortServiceMapEntry.name: gsmpPortServiceMapEntry
gsmpPortServiceMapEntry.description: The entry of this table represents the service lists, which are supported by the specific port.

gsmpMapServiceId.name: gsmpMapServiceId
gsmpMapServiceId.description: This object represents the identifier of the service supported by the switch.

gsmpMapCapSetId.name: gsmpMapCapSetId
gsmpMapCapSetId.description: A capability set contains a set of parameters that describe the QoS parameter values and traffic controls that apply to an instance of the Service.

gsmpTrafficParamIndexNext.name: gsmpTrafficParamIndexNext
gsmpTrafficParamIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value which will be used for gsmpTrafficParamIndex.

gsmpTrafficParamTable.name: gsmpTrafficParamTable
gsmpTrafficParamTable.description: This table contains objects, which specify the traffic parameters of in-segments and out-segments.

gsmpTrafficParamEntry.name: gsmpTrafficParamEntry
gsmpTrafficParamEntry.description: An entry in this table represents the gsmpTrafficParam objects for one or more in or out segments.

gsmpTrafficParamIndex.name: gsmpTrafficParamIndex
gsmpTrafficParamIndex.description: Uniquely identifies this row of this table. Note that zero represents an invalid index.

gsmpTrafficControlsFlags.name: gsmpTrafficControlsFlags
gsmpTrafficControlsFlags.description: This object is used to indicate that specific traffic controls are requested for the requested connection. 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 +-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+ |U|D|I|E|S|V|P|x| +-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+ U: Usage Parameter Control D: Packet Discard I: Ingress Shaping E: Egress Shaping, Peak Rate S: Egress Traffic Shaping, Sustainable Rate V: VC Merge P: Port x: Reserved

gsmpTrafficParamRowStatus.name: gsmpTrafficParamRowStatus
gsmpTrafficParamRowStatus.description: For creating, modifying, and deleting this row.

gsmpTrafficParamStorageType.name: gsmpTrafficParamStorageType
gsmpTrafficParamStorageType.description: Defines the storage type support provided for this object by the agent.

gsmpInSegmentTable.name: gsmpInSegmentTable
gsmpInSegmentTable.description: This table contains a description of the incoming GSMP segments and their associated parameters.

gsmpInSegmentEntry.name: gsmpInSegmentEntry
gsmpInSegmentEntry.description: An entry in this table represents one incoming GSMP segment.

gsmpInSegmentIfIndex.name: gsmpInSegmentIfIndex
gsmpInSegmentIfIndex.description: This is a unique index for an entry in the gsmpInSegmentTable. This value represents the interface index for the incoming GSMP interface. A value of zero represents an incoming label from the per-platform label space.

gsmpInSegmentLabel.name: gsmpInSegmentLabel
gsmpInSegmentLabel.description: The incoming label for this segment.

gsmpInSegmentXCIndex.name: gsmpInSegmentXCIndex
gsmpInSegmentXCIndex.description: Index into gsmpXCTable which identifies which cross-connect entry this segment is part of. A value of zero indicates that this entry is not referred to by any cross-connect entry. When a cross-connect entry is created which this in-segment is a part of, this object is automatically updated to reflect the value of gsmpXCIndex of that cross-connect entry.

gsmpInSegmentOwner.name: gsmpInSegmentOwner
gsmpInSegmentOwner.description: This object denotes the entity that created and is responsible for managing this segment.

gsmpInSegmentTrafficParamPtr.name: gsmpInSegmentTrafficParamPtr
gsmpInSegmentTrafficParamPtr.description: This variable represents a pointer to the traffic parameter specification for this in-segment. This value may point at an entry in the gsmpTrafficParamTable to indicate which gsmpTrafficParamEntry is to be assigned to this segment. This value may optionally point at an externally defined traffic parameter specification table.

gsmpInQoSModelSelector.name: gsmpInQoSModelSelector
gsmpInQoSModelSelector.description: simplePriorityModel(1): The input service selector indicates a simple priority. serviceProfileModel(2): The input service selector is an opaque service profile identifier. Service profiles can be used to indicate pre- defined differentiated service per hop behaviors. serviceModel(3): The input service selector corresponds to a service specification. When the value of this object is serviceModel(3), then a traffic parameters block is appended to this entry. armModel(4): The input service selector corresponds to an ARM service specification. ARM model is defined in qGSMP specification.

gsmpInServiceSelector.name: gsmpInServiceSelector
gsmpInServiceSelector.description: This object identifies details of the service specification being used for connection. The interpretation depends upon the gsmpInQoSModelSelector object.

gsmpInAdaptationMethodType.name: gsmpInAdaptationMethodType
gsmpInAdaptationMethodType.description: The adaptation method is used to define the adaptation framing that may be in use when moving traffic from one port type to another port type; e.g., from a frame relay port to an ATM port.

gsmpInSegmentRowStatus.name: gsmpInSegmentRowStatus
gsmpInSegmentRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

gsmpInSegmentStorageType.name: gsmpInSegmentStorageType
gsmpInSegmentStorageType.description: This variable indicates the storage type for this object.

gsmpOutSegmentTable.name: gsmpOutSegmentTable
gsmpOutSegmentTable.description: This table contains a description of the outgoing GSMP segments to a connection and their associated parameters.

gsmpOutSegmentEntry.name: gsmpOutSegmentEntry
gsmpOutSegmentEntry.description: An entry in this table represents one outgoing GSMP segment.

gsmpOutSegmentIfIndex.name: gsmpOutSegmentIfIndex
gsmpOutSegmentIfIndex.description: This is a unique index for an entry in the gsnmpOutSegmentTable. This value represents the interface index for the outgoing GSMP interface. A value of zero represents an outgoing label from the per-platform label space.

gsmpOutSegmentLabel.name: gsmpOutSegmentLabel
gsmpOutSegmentLabel.description: The outgoing label for this segment.

gsmpOutSegmentXCIndex.name: gsmpOutSegmentXCIndex
gsmpOutSegmentXCIndex.description: Index into gsmpXCTable which identifies which cross-connect entry this segment is part of. A value of zero indicates that this entry is not referred to by any cross-connect entry. When a cross-connect entry is created which this out-segment is a part of, this object is automatically updated to reflect the value of gsmpXCIndex of that cross-connect entry.

gsmpOutSegmentOwner.name: gsmpOutSegmentOwner
gsmpOutSegmentOwner.description: This object denotes the entity that created and is responsible for managing this segment.

gsmpOutSegmentTrafficParamPtr.name: gsmpOutSegmentTrafficParamPtr
gsmpOutSegmentTrafficParamPtr.description: This variable represents a pointer to the traffic parameter specification for this out-segment. This value may point at an entry in the gsmpTrafficParamTable to indicate which gsmpTrafficParamEntry is to be assigned to this segment. This value may optionally point at an externally defined traffic parameter specification table.

gsmpOutQoSModelSelector.name: gsmpOutQoSModelSelector
gsmpOutQoSModelSelector.description: simplePriorityModel(1): The output service selector indicates a simple priority. serviceProfileModel(2): The output service selector is an opaque service profile identifier. Service profiles can be used to indicate pre- defined differentiated service per hop behaviors. serviceModel(3): The output service selector corresponds to a service specification. When the value of this object is serviceModel(3), then a traffic parameters block is appended to this entry. armModel(4): The output service selector corresponds to an ARM service specification. ARM model is defined in qGSMP specification.

gsmpOutAdaptationMethodType.name: gsmpOutAdaptationMethodType
gsmpOutAdaptationMethodType.description: The adaptation method is used to define the adaptation framing that may be in use when moving traffic from one port type to another port type; e.g., from a frame relay port to an ATM port.

gsmpOutSegmentRowStatus.name: gsmpOutSegmentRowStatus
gsmpOutSegmentRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

gsmpOutSegmentStorageType.name: gsmpOutSegmentStorageType
gsmpOutSegmentStorageType.description: This variable indicates the storage type for this object.

gsmpXCIndexNext.name: gsmpXCIndexNext
gsmpXCIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for gsmpXCIndex when creating entries in the gsmpXCTable.

gsmpXCTable.name: gsmpXCTable
gsmpXCTable.description: A connection is modeled as a cross-connect consisting of one or more incoming segments(in-segments) and/or one or more outgoing segments(out-segments) at a switch. The association or interconnection of the in-segments and out-segments is accomplished by using the gsmpXCTable.

gsmpXCEntry.name: gsmpXCEntry
gsmpXCEntry.description: A row in this table represents one cross-connect entry.

gsmpXCIndex.name: gsmpXCIndex
gsmpXCIndex.description: Primary index for the conceptual row identifying cross-connect segments.

gsmpXCIsPersistent.name: gsmpXCIsPersistent
gsmpXCIsPersistent.description: This object denotes whether or not this cross-connect entry and associated in- and out-segments should be restored automatically after failures. This value MUST be set to false in cases where this cross-connect entry was created by a signaling protocol.

gsmpXCOwner.name: gsmpXCOwner
gsmpXCOwner.description: It denotes the entity that created and is responsible for managing this cross-connect.

gsmpXCAdminStatus.name: gsmpXCAdminStatus
gsmpXCAdminStatus.description: The desired operational status of this segment. up(1) = ready to pass packets testing(3) = in some test mode

gsmpXCOperStatus.name: gsmpXCOperStatus
gsmpXCOperStatus.description: The actual operational status of this cross-connect. up(1) = ready to pass packets testing(3) = in some test mode unknown(4) = status cannot be determined for some reason notPresent(6) = some component is missing lowerLayerDown(7) = down due to the state of lower layer interfaces

gsmpConnectType.name: gsmpConnectType
gsmpConnectType.description: This object is used to define connection types.

gsmpBiDirection.name: gsmpBiDirection
gsmpBiDirection.description: If this flag is true, then the connection should be established to be bi-direction.

gsmpXCRowStatus.name: gsmpXCRowStatus
gsmpXCRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

gsmpXCStorageType.name: gsmpXCStorageType
gsmpXCStorageType.description: This variable indicates the storage type for this object.

gsmpInterfacePerfTable.name: gsmpInterfacePerfTable
gsmpInterfacePerfTable.description: This table contains objects to measure the performance of GSMP interfaces and is an AUGMENT to gsmpInterfaceConfTable.

gsmpInterfacePerfEntry.name: gsmpInterfacePerfEntry
gsmpInterfacePerfEntry.description: The Entry of this table contains objects to measure the performance of GSMP interfaces and is an AUGMENT to gsmpInterfaceConfTable.

gsmpInterfaceInFrameCount.name: gsmpInterfaceInFrameCount
gsmpInterfaceInFrameCount.description: This object counts frames arriving at the input. It is relevant for label types = FR and MPLS.

gsmpInterfaceInInvalidLabelCount.name: gsmpInterfaceInInvalidLabelCount
gsmpInterfaceInInvalidLabelCount.description: This object counts frames discarded because their Label is invalid on arrival at an input port.

gsmpInterfaceInFrameDiscardCount.name: gsmpInterfaceInFrameDiscardCount
gsmpInterfaceInFrameDiscardCount.description: This object counts frames discarded due to congestion on an input port. It is relevant for label types = FR and MPLS.

gsmpInterfaceOutFrameCount.name: gsmpInterfaceOutFrameCount
gsmpInterfaceOutFrameCount.description: This object counts frames arriving at the output. It is relevant for label types = FR and MPLS.

gsmpInterfaceOutFrameDiscardCount.name: gsmpInterfaceOutFrameDiscardCount
gsmpInterfaceOutFrameDiscardCount.description: This object counts frames discarded due to congestion on an output port. It is relevant for label types = FR and MPLS.

gsmpLabelPerfTable.name: gsmpLabelPerfTable
gsmpLabelPerfTable.description: This table has objects to measure the performance of connection.

gsmpLabelPerfEntry.name: gsmpLabelPerfEntry
gsmpLabelPerfEntry.description: The Entry of this table contains objects to measure the performance of GSMP label.

gsmpLabelIndex.name: gsmpLabelIndex
gsmpLabelIndex.description: This is a unique index for an entry in the gsmpLabelPerfTable.

gsmpLabelInFrameCount.name: gsmpLabelInFrameCount
gsmpLabelInFrameCount.description: This object counts frames arriving at the in-segment. It is relevant for label types = FR and MPLS.

gsmpLabelInFrameDiscardCount.name: gsmpLabelInFrameDiscardCount
gsmpLabelInFrameDiscardCount.description: This object counts frames discarded due to congestion on the in-segment. It is relevant for label types = FR and MPLS.

gsmpLabelOutFrameCount.name: gsmpLabelOutFrameCount
gsmpLabelOutFrameCount.description: This object counts frames departing from the out-segment. It is relevant for label types = FR and MPLS.

gsmpLabelOutFrameDiscardCount.name: gsmpLabelOutFrameDiscardCount
gsmpLabelOutFrameDiscardCount.description: This object counts frames discarded due to congestion on the out-segment. It is relevant for label types = FR and MPLS.
